Task: Session Cleanup & State Reset
Navigate to Main Menu (setCurrentIndex(0))

Description: Redirects the user back to the initial player-selection screen. 
By setting the index of the QStackedWidget to 0, the application instantly displays the very first page that was added to the stack (the main menu).

Detach the Active Game Board (removeWidget)

Description: Unlinks the dynamically generated game board (self.hra_widget) from the application's screen manager.
This ensures the finished game session is no longer a part of the active widget deck.

Memory Management & Garbage Collection (deleteLater)

Description: Safely destroys the old game board widget and frees up system memory. 
This is a critical step to prevent memory leaks; without it, repeatedly starting and exiting games would keep adding invisible widgets to the RAM, 
eventually slowing down or crashing the application.
